therian.operator.convert

Class NOPConverter

  • java.lang.Object
    • therian.operator.FromSourceToTarget
      • therian.operator.convert.AbstractConverter
        • therian.operator.convert.Converter.WithDynamicTarget<Object>
          • therian.operator.convert.NOPConverter
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Operator<Convert<? extends Object,?>>, FromSourceToTarget.FromSource<Object>

    @Reusable(value=SUPPORT_CHECK)
@StandardOperator
public class NOPConverter
extends Converter.WithDynamicTarget<Object>
    Uses source value as target value when assignable. This is a so-called "standard converter," but a more strongly typed Converter can be specified for any given datatype that requires a new instance. Some type of CopyingConverter is recommended for this purpose.
    See Also:
    Operators.standard()
